The paper deals with spectrum allocation and user association in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses scalability and optimization, which are topics related to distributed computing and machine learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper proposes a convex relaxation method, which is a technique used in optimization and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
